Reasoning: 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper discusses the use of a fuel cycle simulator and the effects of modeling choices on fuel cycle dynamics. This falls under the domain of computational engineering and science. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper discusses the use of the Cyclus fuel cycle simulator and its plug-in capability, which involves the development of mathematical software. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the behavior of different fuel cycle scenarios under supply-constraint pressure, which can be seen as a control problem. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper mentions the market-like dynamic material routing capability of the Cyclus fuel cycle simulator, which can be seen as an application of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the effects of modeling choices on fuel cycle dynamics, which can be seen as a software engineering problem.
